      "writtenOn": "2017-05-19T20:44:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think so. I posted to https://groups.google.com/a/webmproject.org/forum/#!msg/webp-discuss/2rFPKOzxuSM/uabYhmSNJAAJ where they told you it was just a hint to try to get some clarity. Sometimes WEBPImageDecoder uses WebPIterator.has_alpha, and sometimes it checks the FORMAT_FLAGS, which checks whether there is alpha in any frame. This corresponds to whether the iterator (i.e. a specific frame) has alpha. (On that note, I\u0027ve changed it to use the iterator, which I use elsewhere.)\n\nAlthough they\u0027re just hints, they should be correct coming from libwebp, and actually treating them as correct may convince encoders to use the properly.",
