    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c8317e93_e201007a",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWebpCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 403,
      "author": {
        "id": 5185
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-05-15T19:59:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can we also skip blending if the disposal method if RestoreBGColor?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 403,
        "startChar": 15,
        "endLine": 403,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "6e76d53e5eec6445e64e7498edf48c138971c8fd",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "73616f45_d1528c0b",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWebpCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 403,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-05-19T20:44:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If the prior frame is RestoreBGColor, and this frame is contained within that frame, then yes. I don\u0027t know whether that case happens enough to make it worth the extra complexity. (In that case, this frame should probably not be WEBP_MUX_BLEND, but we know encoders can use dumb combinations.)\n\nIf the prior frame was RestoreBGColor and fills the image, this frame is marked independent, so we will skip blending.\n\nI did realize that we can skip blending if the frame is opaque, though.",
      "parentUuid": "c8317e93_e201007a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 403,
        "startChar": 15,
        "endLine": 403,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "6e76d53e5eec6445e64e7498edf48c138971c8fd",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f7de6b3c_09f5f160",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWebpCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 517,
      "author": {
        "id": 5185
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-05-15T19:59:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If the color space is non-null and fPremulBehavior is kRespect, I think we need to decode to unpremul here.  I believe that libwebp has implemented a kIgnore style premultiply.\n\nI know we typically can\u0027t draw unpremul, but for some reason I think the SW color correct drawing impl does support unpremul.  mtklein@ would know for sure.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 517,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 517,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "6e76d53e5eec6445e64e7498edf48c138971c8fd",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d0bab18e_632305bf",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWebpCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 517,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-05-19T20:44:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e If the color space is non-null and fPremulBehavior is kRespect, I think we need to decode to unpremul here.  I believe that libwebp has implemented a kIgnore style premultiply.\n\nThis case got absorbed into the above, since we\u0027re using SkRasterPipeline now. The above case properly tells libwebp to use unpremul.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e I know we typically can\u0027t draw unpremul, but for some reason I think the SW color correct drawing impl does support unpremul.  mtklein@ would know for sure.\n\nAs discussed in person, an SkCanvas won\u0027t let you do this, but SkRasterPipeline does!",
      "parentUuid": "f7de6b3c_09f5f160",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 517,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 517,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "6e76d53e5eec6445e64e7498edf48c138971c8fd",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
